HEADWORD: Fatherland
<hw>Fa"ther*land"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Imitated fr. D.
<ets>vaderland</ets>. See <er>Father</er>, and <er>Land</er>.]</ety>
<def>One's native land; the native land of one's fathers or
ancestors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

